translated: Klint, Axel Edvard, contract vicar, Källunge, born on April 7, 1882 in Follingbo, Gotland. Son of the pastor Ludvig K. and Maria Hägström. Married on August 29, m. Elin Siggelin. Children: Gösta born in 1929, studying engineering, Ebbe born in 1931, studying at Visby high school, Elsa born in 1932, studying at the same, Anna born in 1935, studying at Visby trade school, Agneta born in 1937, Karin born in 1944, Margareta born in 1946. Completed exams in Visby in 1900, theology degree in 1901, theological candidacy, practical theological examination, and ordained as a priest in Visby diocese in 1905. Received theological license in 1911. Served as hospital chaplain and military church adjutant in 1906, on leave for studies from 1907-1911, acting pastor in Hangvar from 1911, temporary parish priest in Källunge from 1912, popular education inspector from 1914, parish priest in Källunge, Vallstena, Hejnum, and Bäl since 1932, contract vicar in Gotland northern contract since 1937. Also served as a member of the central board of the Swedish Association of Priests from 1938-1946, chairman of the Christian Student Association in Visby Diocese, and Hejnum's and Bäl's church assembly as well as Källunge and Vadstena school council. President of the clergy meeting in 1947. Leased Källunge Wage Cottage from 1912-1944. Awarded the Illustrious Order of the North Star (LVO).
